Thank you for your feedback! Part of the in-universe translation process for their language involves putting their abstract concepts into human naming conventions. While dark matter creatures undoubtedly have their own terminology for the way they move across the Higgs field, it seemed logical that the Foundation would put it into terms familiar to their researchers and translate their naming conventions into ours, when there is an unambiguous one-to-one relation between the two.







